1
00:00:03,110 --> 00:00:06,594
Watch this video to learn how
to set up Wi-Fi and Bluetooth

2
00:00:06,651 --> 00:00:12,202
on your Samsung Galaxy
Tab 4 10.1 from Verizon.

3
00:00:12,242 --> 00:00:17,783
Open the Notification Panel by touching and
sliding down from the top of the screen.

4
00:00:17,830 --> 00:00:21,600
Tap the Settings icon.

5
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:24,830
Then, tap Wi-Fi.

6
00:00:24,877 --> 00:00:33,552
Make sure Wi-Fi is turned on by sliding
the Wi-Fi switch to the right.

7
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:38,742
Wi-Fi will turn on and a list of
nearby Wi-Fi networks will appear.

8
00:00:38,781 --> 00:00:43,330
Tap the one you
want to connect to.

9
00:00:43,386 --> 00:00:48,872
If you’re connecting to a secure network,
you’ll need to enter its password.

10
00:00:48,912 --> 00:00:53,376
Once done, tap Connect.

11
00:00:53,448 --> 00:00:57,724
You should now see Connected
underneath the network name.

12
00:00:57,780 --> 00:01:01,958
Now let’s look at connecting a
Bluetooth device to your tablet.

13
00:01:02,022 --> 00:01:05,768
To set up Bluetooth,
tap Bluetooth.

14
00:01:05,824 --> 00:01:13,506
Make sure Bluetooth is turned on by sliding
the Bluetooth switch to the right.

15
00:01:13,609 --> 00:01:19,924
Tap Scan to get an updated list
of nearby Bluetooth devices.

16
00:01:20,006 --> 00:01:24,244
Please note that the device you are attempting
to pair with must be in discovery mode

17
00:01:24,356 --> 00:01:26,646
or the scan will not find it.

18
00:01:26,741 --> 00:01:31,379
Once you have found the device you
want to pair with, select it.

19
00:01:31,483 --> 00:01:35,497
You may need to confirm an already
existing password for pairing.

20
00:01:35,577 --> 00:01:40,444
 If this is the case, tap OK.

21
00:01:40,523 --> 00:01:46,531
On the tablet, connected devices will
appear in the paired devices list.

22
00:01:46,618 --> 00:01:51,010
Press the Home button
when complete.

23
00:01:51,066 --> 00:01:53,588
To quickly turn
Bluetooth on or off,

24
00:01:53,627 --> 00:01:55,750
you can use the
Notification Panel

25
00:01:55,813 --> 00:02:00,590
by touching and sliding your finger
down from the top of the screen.

26
00:02:00,646 --> 00:02:06,968
Then, tap the Bluetooth icon.